# Documentation, Index & Status Maintenance

**MANDATORY after every code-modifying prompt.** Update ONLY the affected sections, never rewrite a whole file. Do this BEFORE ending your turn (before or after commit, but always before responding to user).

## PROJECT_STATUS.md (read at session start, update after EVERY code change)
Sections: Snapshot, File Map, Decision Log (dated), Current Parameters, Known Issues, **Agent Context** (last prompt, active decisions, what changed this session, next steps, blockers — keep < 15 lines).
- **Agent Context** must always reflect the LATEST state — overwrite previous session's content.
- Add a **Decision Log** entry (dated) for any architectural/algorithm/strategy change.

## CODE_INDEX.md (grep-only, never read in full)
Update when: a file is created, an export is added/removed/renamed, a file is moved/deleted, or key line numbers shift > ±5.
Do NOT update for body-only edits, comments, formatting.
Entry format: `### path (N lines)` + table `| Line | Export | Kind |`.
Efficiency: never re-scan the project — grep the file's exports, update its table + line count.

## Reference docs (update only when relevant)
- `docs/Documentation.md` — every external API (endpoint, params, example req/resp) and every custom algorithm (Gaussian, PoP, smart_bary, etc.) must be documented in markdown.
- `docs/Project.md` — milestones / current task / TODO·IN PROGRESS·DONE (historical; PROJECT_STATUS.md is the live one).
- `docs/Milestone-Backlog-Ameliorations.md` — when an idea moves to EN COURS / FAIT, tick its item and fill `Décision`.
- `docs/index.json` — grep-based doc index; keep entries current.

## Logs
- `this.log` (or `legacy/this.log`) holds runtime debug output pasted by the user when needed.
